<title type="html"><![CDATA[Is there any NES emulator reusable library?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5976&amp;p=55603#p55603"><![CDATA[
I'm wondering if there are NES emulators that instead of being a full running application, are reusable libraries you can interface with to make a working emulator. This way you can add specific functionality to the emulation.<br />Because the NES emulation should always be the same, working exactly (or as close as it can get) to the NES's original way of working.<br />So do you know any? if there's none I'm gonna build it.<br /><br />My idea is that this library has a class you can instantiate and get a full virtual NES running, it should be 100% platform independent, and also implementation independent, meaning it wouldn't output any sound, music or graphics, but have callbacks that you can plug in to implement those outputs.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3773">Petruza</a> — Sat Jan 23, 2010 4:27 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
